he%20repeatedly%20ignored%20court%20orders%20in%20their%20federal%20defamation%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20he's%20found%20in%20contempt%2C%20Trump%20could%20not%20issue%20a%20pardon%20or%20commute%20his%20sentence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERudy%20Giuliani%20took%20the%20witness%20stand%20in%20federal%20court%20in%20New%20York%20on%20Friday%2C%20battling%20a%20potential%20contempt-of-court%20finding%20sought%20by%20two%20Georgia%20election%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Donald%20Trump%20can't%20come%20to%20his%20rescue%20if%20he%20loses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20judge%20decides%20Giuliani%20has%20flouted%20court%20orders%20by%20failing%20to%20turn%20over%20assets%20and%20evidence%20in%20the%20three-year-old%20defamation%20case%2C%20he%20could%20fine%20Giuliani%20or%20send%20him%20to%20jail%20until%20he%20complies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20pardon%20and%20commutation%20powers%20Trump%20regains%20on%20his%20return%20to%20the%20White%20House%20next%20month%20do%20not%20extend%20to%20civil%20contempt%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20experts%20in%20constitutional%20law%20and%20federal%20pardons%2C%20Giuliani%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20rely%20on%20his%20former%20client%20to%20save%20him%20from%20jail%20or%20fines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGenerally%20criminal%20contempt%20is%20within%20the%20power%20of%20the%20president%2C%20but%20civil%20contempt%20is%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Margaret%20Love%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20served%20as%20the%20Justice%20Department%20pardon%20attorney%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20was%20combative%20on%20the%20stand%20on%20Friday%2C%20at%20a%20daylong%20contempt-of-court%20hearing%20overseen%20by%20US%20District%20Judge%20Lewis%20Liman%20in%20a%20courthouse%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%2C%20which%20will%20continue%20next%20week%2C%20is%20part%20of%20a%20suite%20of%20civil%20cases%20brought%20by%20mother-daughter%20Georgia%20election%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frudy-giuliani-trial-jury-verdict-defamation-damages-georgia-election-workers-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERuby%20Freeman%20and%20Wandrea%20%26quot%3BShaye%26quot%3B%20Moss%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20monstrously%20overbroad%2C%26quot%3B%20Giuliani%20complained%20of%20Moss-Freeman%20asset-document%20requests%20during%20questioning%20at%20one%20point%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20abusive%20and%20overbroad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20found%20in%202023%20that%20Giuliani%20defamed%20the%20pair%20%E2%80%94%20and%20subjected%20them%20to%20a%20barrage%20of%20racist%20death%20threats%20%E2%80%94%20by%20repeatedly%20and%20falsely%20accusing%20them%20of%20voter%20fraud%2C%20including%20by%20lying%20that%20they%20had%20tallied%20suitcases%20full%20of%20illegal%20ballots%20for%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20a%20jury%20ordered%20Giuliani%20to%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frudy-giuliani-mother-daughter-defamation-victims-still-owed-millions-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFreeman%20and%20Moss%20%24148%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20recent%20weeks%2C%20the%20two%20plaintiffs%20have%20sought%20to%20have%20him%20held%20in%20contempt%20in%20DC%20and%20in%20Manhattan%20to%20force%20him%20to%20comply%20with%20judges'%20demands%20that%20he%20cease%20defaming%20them%20and%20turn%20over%20assets%20and%20evidence%20as%20ordered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contempt%20hearing%20is%20scheduled%20to%20continue%20Monday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani's%20defense%20has%20focused%20on%20his%20recent%20switch%20of%20lawyers%20from%20Kenneth%20Caruso%2C%20an%20experienced%20New%20York-based%20attorney%20he%20has%20known%20for%20nearly%2050%20years%2C%20to%20Joseph%20Cammarata%2C%20best%20known%20for%20representing%20a%20woman%20who%20accused%20former%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20of%20sexual%20misconduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20swapped%20lawyers%20sometime%20in%20November.%20Giuliani%20said%20that%20changing%20attorneys%20had%20made%20it%20a%20challenge%20to%20meet%20deadlines%20%E2%80%94%20an%20excuse%20that%20the%20pair's%20lawyers%20did%20not%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECammarata%20said%20in%20court%20Friday%20that%20his%20client%20has%20completed%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20compliance%26quot%3B%20with%20his%20obligations%20and%20should%20not%20be%20held%20in%20contempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20Giuliani%2C%20who%20is%2080%20years%20old%2C%20has%20struggled%20to%20deal%20with%20an%20avalanche%20of%20legal%20proceedings%20against%20him%2C%20including%20criminal%20investigations.%20Prosecutors%20in%20Arizona%20and%20Georgia%20have%20brought%20cases%20against%20Giuliani%20over%20his%20attempts%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20of%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%20on%20behalf%20of%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMayor%20Giuliani%2C%20as%20this%20court%20knows%2C%20has%20multiple%20litigations%20going%20on%20in%20multiple%20states%2C%20both%20civil%20and%20criminal%20in%20nature%2C%26quot%3B%20Cammarata%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20took%20the%20stand%20%E2%80%94%20struggling%20up%20a%20step%20by%20the%20podium%20%E2%80%94%20after%20the%20court's%20lunch%20break.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20break%2C%20he%20complained%20to%20Jane%20Rosenberg%2C%20a%20courtroom%20artist%2C%20about%20how%20she%20depicted%20him%20in%20one%20of%20her%20pastel%20drawings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20made%20me%20look%20like%20my%20dog%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20her%2C%20Rosenberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20was%20cross-examined%20by%20Meryl%20Conant%20Governski%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Freeman%20and%20Moss%2C%20about%20two%20sworn%20declarations%20he%20had%20submitted%20to%20the%20court%20saying%20that%20he's%20abided%20by%20all%20of%20the%20judge's%20orders%20and%20provided%20proper%20responses%20to%20information%20requests%20and%20interrogatories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20turnaround%20time%20required%20for%20discovery%20requests%20was%20%26quot%3Bunusually%20short%26quot%3B%20even%20though%20his%20previous%20attorney%2C%20Caruso%2C%20had%20agreed%20to%20the%2014-day%20response%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20morning%2C%20Cammarata%20cross-examined%20Aaron%20Nathan%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Freeman%20and%20Moss%2C%20over%20how%20he%20determined%20whether%20the%20former%20New%20York%20mayor%20had%20failed%20to%20account%20for%20his%20property.%20Many%20of%20the%20questions%20concerned%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frudy-giuliani-hiding-assets-election-workers-joe-dimaggio-apartment-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGiuliani's%20framed%20Joe%20DiMaggio%20jersey%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20once%20hung%20over%20the%20fireplace%20in%20his%20Manhattan%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nathan%20gained%20access%20to%20the%20apartment%20in%20October%20and%20searched%20the%20residence%2C%20it%20was%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20jersey%20has%20been%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Cammarata%20said%20in%20one%20heated%20moment.%20%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20accusations%20that%20my%20client%20absconded%20with%20the%20jersey.%20And%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECammarata%2C%20in%20winding%20and%20plodding%20cross-examination%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20photo%20of%20the%20jersey%20in%20the%20apartment%20was%20taken%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202023%2C%20and%20time%20had%20passed%20before%20Nathan%20went%20into%20the%20apartment%20and%20saw%20the%20location%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20honor%2C%20if%20I%20may%2C%20I%20want%20to%20take%20his%20testimony%20about%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Cammarata%20objected%20after%20the%20judge%20cut%20off%20his%20questioning%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20before%20Friday's%20hearing%2C%20Giuliani%20asked%20for%20permission%20to%20attend%20virtually%2C%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bmedical%20issues%20with%20his%20left%20knee%20and%20breathing%20problems%20due%20to%20lung%20issues%20discovered%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20his%20lawyer%2C%20explained%20it%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20breathing%20problems%20are%20%26quot%3Battributable%20to%20Defendant%20Rudolph%20W.%20Giuliani%20being%20at%20the%20World%20Trade%20Center%20site%20on%20September%2011%2C%202001%2C%26quot%3B%20Cammarata%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20attended%20in%20person%20after%20the%20judge%20warned%20he'd%20otherwise%20be%20barred%20from%20testifying%20on%20his%20own%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20Giuliani%20be%20found%20in%20contempt%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20executive%20pardon%20power%20would%20not%20extend%20to%20a%20civil%20contempt%20sentence%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20in%20a%20federal%20court%2C%20said%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20Ephraim%20Savitt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Giuliani's%20jailing%20wouldn't%20be%20a%20punishment%20for%20a%20past%20infraction%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20remedial%20sentence%2C%20meant%20to%20force%20his%20compliance%20with%20the%20judge's%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCivil%20contempt%20sentences%20are%20essentially%20open-ended%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20Giuliani%20could%20only%20be%20freed%20once%20he%20had%20complied%2C%20said%20Savitt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20means%20of%20coercing%20a%20party%20to%20take%20some%20action%2C%20to%20compel%20compliance%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michel%20Paradis%2C%20who%20teaches%20constitutional%20law%20at%20Columbia%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20long%20as%20Giuliani%20has%20the%20keys%20to%20his%20own%20cell%2C%20and%20can%20be%20freed%20by%20simply%20complying%20with%20the%20judge's%20order%2C%20then%20there%20is%20no%20crime%20to%20be%20pardoned%20or%20punishment%20to%20be%20reprieved%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adde