of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20restaurant%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20make%20that%20back.%20%26quot%3BUnless%20we%20have%20somebody%20inject%20money%20that%20we%20lost%2C%20we%20don't%20recuperate%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Hernandez%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc2d52aa-8661-447c-ac8d-8c052ec794ca%5C%22%3EPuerto%20Rico's%20power%20company%20warns%20of%20more%20outages%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELuma%20Energy%2C%20the%20private%20company%20that%20transmits%20and%20distributes%20power%20in%20the%20territory%2C%20said%20in%20an%20X%20post%20on%20Thursday%20morning%20that%2099%25%20of%20its%201.4%20million%20customers%20were%20back%20in%20service.%20It%20didn't%20respond%20to%20multiple%20inquiries%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20urged%20customers%20to%20limit%20their%20energy%20consumption%20and%20use%20backup%20energy%20wherever%20possible%20as%20the%20electric%20system%20gets%20back%20up%20to%20speed.%20Luma%20initially%20attributed%20the%20blackout%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20an%20underground%20cable%2C%20but%20said%20on%20Thursday%20the%20cause%20was%20still%20under%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20island-wide%20blackout%2C%20which%20happened%20around%20dawn%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20threw%20the%20New%20Year's%20Eve%20plans%20of%20the%20territory's%20more%20than%203%20million%20residents%20into%20disarray.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20of%20another%20restaurant%20in%20San%20Juan%2C%20who%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20lost%20about%20a%20thousand%20dollars%20worth%20of%20refrigerated%20items%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20produce%20and%20fish%20%E2%80%94%20when%20the%20power%20went%20out%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20she%20said%2C%20the%20restaurant%20was%20already%20closed%20that%20day%2C%20but%20because%20she%20doesn't%20have%20backup%20generators%2C%20she%20couldn't%20save%20her%20perishable%20inventory.%20And%20her%20restaurant's%20margins%20are%20already%20very%20slim%2C%20she%20said%2C%20so%20it%20won't%20be%20easy%20to%20make%20back%20that%20lost%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20San%20Juan%20without%20power%20on%20New%20Year's%20Eve%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67784a4a59d276c1cdaffef6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESan%20Juan%20could%20be%20seen%20from%20the%20air%20without%20power.%20Some%20people%20have%20generators%2C%20but%20many%20business%20owners%20were%20left%20scrambling.%3Cp%3ERicardo%20Arduengo%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHotels%2C%20too%2C%20lost%20money%20during%20this%20week's%20power%20outage.%20Jose%20Lopez%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20small%20eight-room%20hotel%20Villa%20Herencia%2C%20where%20he%20works%20in%20San%20Juan%2C%20had%20to%20refund%20a%20few%20guests%20who%20left%20early%20during%20Tuesday's%20outage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20said%2C%20power%20service%20has%20been%20good%20since%20it%20was%20restored%2C%20and%20the%20hotel%20hasn't%20experienced%20any%20smaller%20outages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20caf%C3%A9%20worker%20in%20San%20Juan%2C%20who%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20that%20while%20his%20caf%C3%A9%20suffered%20some%20losses%20this%20week%2C%20it%20was%20able%20to%20continue%20operating%20through%20the%20blackout%20thanks%20to%20its%20generator.%20People%20from%20around%20the%20neighborhood%20were%20able%20to%20come%20in%20and%20get%20food%20during%20the%20outage%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20some%20businesses%20and%20residences%20had%20their%20power%20restored%20by%20Tuesday%20afternoon%20or%20evening%2C%20others%20had%20to%20wait%20longer.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpuerto-rico-i-moved-constant-power-outages-hate-why-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERyan%20Pamplin%2C%20a%2036-year-old%20business%20owner%3C