20interest%20of%20justice%2C%20instead%20setting%20a%20January%2010%20sentencing%20date%20%E2%80%94%20just%2010%20days%20before%20the%20inauguration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%2018-page%20ruling%2C%20State%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Juan%20Merchan%20gave%20Trump%20the%20choice%20of%20appearing%20in%20person%20in%20his%20Manhattan%20courtroom%20or%20virtually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20also%20said%20he%20is%20inclined%20to%20sentence%20Trump%20to%20zero%20penalties%20%E2%80%94%20what's%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bunconditional%20discharge%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20no%20jail%20term%2C%20no%20fines%2C%20no%20community%20service%2C%20no%20probation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20sentence%20would%20honor%20Trump's%20concerns%20about%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20transition%20and%20pending%20presidency%2C%20as%20well%20as%20reflect%20prosecutors'%20view%20that%20jail%20is%20not%20a%20practical%20sentencing%20recommendation%2C%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Trump's%20arguments%20failed%20to%20justify%20the%20outright%20dismissal%20of%20the%20indictment%20or%20overturning%20the%20jury's%20May%2030%20verdict%2C%20the%20judge%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20arguments%20were%20%26quot%3Bunpersuasive%20as%20no%20compelling%20factor%2C%20consideration%20or%20circumstance%20submitted%20demonstrate%20that%20imposition%20of%20sentence%20would%20result%20in%20injustice%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25476753-ny-v-trump-merchan-interest-of-justice-decision-2025%2F%3Fembed%3D1%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20called%20the%20case%20a%20politically-motivated%20witch%20hunt%20%E2%80%94%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20is%20a%20democrat%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20lawyers%20have%20promised%20to%20exhaust%20both%20his%20state%20and%20federal%20appellate%20options%20in%20hopes%20of%20clearing%20his%20rap%20sheet%20of%20the%20historic%20conviction.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20spokesperson%20Steven%20Cheung%20called%20Merchan's%20decision%20%26quot%3Ba%20direct%20violation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Immunity%20decision%20and%20other%20longstanding%20jurisprudence.%20This%20lawless%20case%20should%20have%20never%20been%20brought%20and%20the%20Constitution%20demands%20that%20it%20be%20immediately%20dismissed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20must%20be%20allowed%20to%20continue%20the%20Presidential%20Transition%20process%20and%20to%20execute%20the%20vital%20duties%20of%20the%20presidency%2C%20unobstructed%20by%20the%20remains%20of%20this%20or%20any%20remnants%20of%20the%20Witch%20Hunts.%20There%20should%20be%20no%20sentencing%2C%20and%20President%20Trump%20will%20continue%20fighting%20against%20these%20hoaxes%20until%20they%20are%20all%20dead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22def752f7-bd99-496a-acc6-d857d4b492f4%5C%22%3EThree%20prior%20sentencing%20delays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20sentencing%20has%20been%20delayed%20three%20times%20in%20the%20half-year%20since%20a%20Manhattan%20jury%20found%20he%20falsified%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hush-money-trial-verdict-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20Organization%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%20throughout%20his%20first%20year%20in%20office%20to%20retroactively%20hide%20a%20%24130%2C000%20hush-money%20payment%20that%20silenced%20porn%20actress%20Stormy%20Daniels%2011%20days%20before%20the%202016%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20first%20sentencing%20date%2C%20July%2011%2C%20was%20scratched%20to%20allow%20time%20for%20a%20back-and-forth%20over%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-january-6-election-ruling-decision-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Supreme%20Court's%20July%201%20presidential%20immunity%3C%2Fa%3E%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20sentencing%20date%2C%20September%2018%2C%20was%20scuttled%20after%20Trump%20argued%20it%20was%20too%20close%20to%20the%20November%205%20election.%20The%20third%20date%2C%20November%2026%2C%20was%20ditched%20because%20the%20parties%20needed%20time%20to%20litigate%20the%20next%20steps%20triggered%20by%20his%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20had%20faced%20up%20to%20four%20years%20in%20prison%20at%20sentencing%2C%20though%20former%20New%20York%20judges%20called%20it%20unlikely%20that%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20a%2078-year-old%20non-violent%20felon%20with%20no%20prior%20criminal%20record%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-judges-weigh-in-on-trump-hush-money-sentencing-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20be%20sent%20to%20jail%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Any%20sentence%20%E2%80%94%20including%20probation%20and%20community%20service%20%E2%80%94%20would%20almost%20certainly%20be%20stayed%20during%20the%20yearslong%20appeal%20process%2C%20they%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20Trump%20has%20sought%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20times%20to%20dismiss%20the%20hush%20money%20case%20on%20various%20grounds%2C%20to%20convince%20the%20judge%20to%20recuse%20himself%2C%20and%20to%20have%20the%20case%20transferred%20to%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20dismissal%20motion%20from%20early%20December%2C%20his%20lawyers%20argued%20without%20success%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffighting-hush-money-case-trump-says-presidents-elect-are-immune-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Trump%20has%20presidential%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20%3C%2Fa%3Enow%2C%20as%20president-elect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20rejected%20that%20bid%20two%20weeks%20later%2C%20finding%20that%20the%20hush-money%20case%20hinged%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hush-money-conviction-survives-immunity-challenge-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bdecidedly%20personal%20acts%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20plus%20copious%20non-official-act%20evidence%20of%20guilt%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20exempt%20from%20presidential%20immunity%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f4e011d-0b25-443e-9c3c-d23daba31873%5C%22%3EInterest-of-justice%20dismissal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nysenate.gov%2Flegislation%2Flaws%2FCPL%2F210.40%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfurtherance%20of%20justice%26quot%3B%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20lets%20a%20judge%20dismiss%20a%20conviction%20or%20indictment%20when%2C%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bsome%20compelling%20factor%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20continuing%20the%20case%20%26quot%3Bwould%20constitute%20or%20result%20in%20injustice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20compelling%20factor%20is%20Trump's%20pending%20presidency%2C%20his%20lawyers%20argued%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Bragg's%20side%20countered%20that%20Trump%20has%20not%20met%20the%20high%20legal%20bar%20for%20an%20interest-of-justice%20dismissal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20law%2C%20a%20judge%20must%20weigh%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20offense%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bhistory%2C%20character%20and%20condition%20of%20the%20defendant%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20impact%20of%20a%20dismissal%20upon%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20public%20in%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d43e240a-0acb-42aa-85c0-7719f6f3d394%5C%22%3EThe%20Constitution's%20Supremacy%20Clause%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20latest%20dismissal%20bid%2C%20Trump's%20lawyers%20also%20referenced%20the%20US%20Constitution's%20Supremacy%20Clause%2C%20citing%20case%20law%20they%20said%20bars%20%26quot%3Bhostile%20state%20courts%26quot%3B%20from%20interfering%20with%20th