0-%20there%20are%20serious%20concerns%20of%20another%20health%20crisis%20after%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeijing%20however%2C%20has%20downplayed%20the%20developments%20in%20recent%20days%2C%20passing%20it%20off%20as%20an%20annual%20occurrence%20in%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20international%20reports%20cautioned%20travelers%20to%20reconsider%20their%20travel%20plans%20to%20China%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20Beijing%20issued%20a%20press%20statement%20to%20address%20such%20concerns.%20China's%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Mao%20Ning%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20%26quot%3BRespiratory%20infections%20tend%20to%20peak%20during%20the%20winter%20season%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReassuring%20citizens%20and%20tourists%2C%20she%20said%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20assure%20you%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20cares%20about%20the%20health%20of%20Chinese%20citizens%20and%20foreigners%20coming%20to%20China%26quot%3B%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20safe%20to%20travel%20in%20China%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20overcrowded%20hospitals%20and%20reports%20of%20the%20surge%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%2C%20she%20said%20%26quot%3BThe%20diseases%20appears%20to%20be%20less%20severe%20and%20spread%20with%20a%20smaller%20scale%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%26quot%3B.%20She%20also%20urged%20citizens%20and%20tourists%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20guidelines%20issued%20by%20the%20National%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20Administration%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20days%20there%20has%20been%20a%20sudden%20spike%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%20across%20China%2C%20reminding%20people%20of%20a%20similar%20surge%20during%20COVID-19.%20The%20media%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%20like%20Indonesia%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Japan%20also%20cautioned%20its%20citizens%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20situation%20in%20China%20and%20take%20needed%20precautions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHospitals%20in%20China%20have%20been%20overwhelmed%20by%20cases%20of%20HMPV%2C%20influenza%20A%2C%20Mycoplasma%20pneumoniae%2C%20and%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20IS%20HUMAN%20METAPNEUMOVIRUS%20or%20HMPV%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHMPV%20causes%20flu-like%20symptoms%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20severe%20respiratory%20issues%2C%20especially%20among%20children%20and%20vulnerable%20groups.%20It%20is%20a%20respiratory%20virus%20that%20causes%20upper%20and%20lower%20respiratory%20infections.%20The%20disease%20was%20first%20identified%20in%202001%2C%20however%2C%20there%20is%20no%20vaccine%20developed%20to%20prevent%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20symptoms%20of%20HMPV%20are%20similar%20to%20those%20of%20flu%2C%20like%20cough%2C%20fever%2C%20nasal%20congestion%20and%20shortness%20of%20breath.%20However%2C%20in%20severe%20cases%2C%20the%20virus%20can%20lead%20to%20complications%20like%20bronchitis%20or%20pneumonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20how%20severe%20a%20case%20is%2C%20the%20incubation%20period%20usually%20lasts%203-7%20days%20and%20full%20recovery%20may%20take%20a%20few%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHMPV%20is%20a%20communicable%20disease%2C%20which%20means%20it%20can%20spread%20through%20the%20air%20as%20well%20as%20through%20touch.%20Coughing%20or%20sneezing%20can%20spread%20it.%20The%20virus%20stays%20active%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20objects%20at%20room%20temperature%2C%20so%20touching%20such%20an%20object%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20getting%20the%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20similar%20to%20Covid%20in%20many%20ways.%20Some%20of%20the%20similarities%20being%20that%20they%20both%20are%20respiratory%20illnesses%20and%20lead%20to%20coughing%2C%20fever%2C%20congestion%2C%20sore%20throat%20and%20shortness%20of%20breath.%20They%20both%20spread%20through%20respiratory%20droplets.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735932240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Fsgep8sro_china-covid_625x300_09_January_