%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20reiterated%20time%20and%20again%20that%20%26quot%3Bterror%20and%20talks%26quot%3B%20cannot%20go%20together%2C%20and%20urged%20Pakistan%20to%20stop%20cross%20border%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relationship%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20came%20to%20a%20halt%20after%20the%202019%20Pulwama%20Attack.%20Pakistan%20also%20downgraded%20the%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20India%20after%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDar%20also%20announced%20plans%20to%20visit%20Bangladesh%20next%20month%2C%20aiming%20to%20strengthen%20economic%20and%20trade%20cooperation.%20He%20described%20Bangladesh%20as%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20lost%20brother%26quot%3B%20and%20noted%20that%20Islamabad%20and%20Dhaka%20are%20rebuilding%20ties%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%20last%20year%2C%20on%20August%205%2C%20after%20a%20student-led%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDar%20also%20rejected%20claims%20of%20the%20country's%20isolation%20as%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20assumed%20office%2C%20there%20was%20a%20perception%20of%20diplomatic%20isolation.%20However%2C%20by%20expanding%20our%20diplomatic%20reach%20and%20engaging%20with%20regional%20neighbours%2C%20this%20perception%20has%20changed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Dar%20addressed%20Pakistan's%20relations%20with%20Afghanistan%2C%20expressing%20a%20desire%20to%20strengthen%20ties%20despite%20the%20challenge%20of%20terrorism.%20He%20criticised%20former%20intelligence%20chief%20Gen%20Faiz%20Hameed%20for%20engaging%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20Tehreek-e-Taliban%20Pakistan%20(TTP)%20and%20revealed%20that%20planned%20visits%20to%20Kabul%20were%20postponed%20due%20to%20terrorist%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Pakistan%20has%20been%20facing%20a%20rise%20in%20terrorism%20since%202021%2C%20when%20the%20Afghan%20Taliban%20came%20to%20power%2C%20and%20they%20have%20demanded%20that%20Afghanistan%20should%20control%20the%20terrorists%20who%20are%20operating%20on%20their%20soil%20against%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20developments%2C%20Dar%20highlighted%20progress%20in%20Pakistan's%20nuclear%20energy%20sector%2C%20announcing%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20Chashma%205%20(C-5)%20nuclear%20power%20project.%20He%20also%20confirmed%20the%20appointment%20of%20former%20Foreign%20Secretary%20Sohail%20Mahmood%20as%20Secretary%20General%20of%20the%20D-8%20Developing%20Eight%20Forum.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735923540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fbk3uh6qg_india-pak-ians_625x300_03_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frelevant-t-word-is-terrorism-not-tango-india-on-pak-deputy-pms-remark-7393760%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20took%20a%20jibe%20at%20Pakistan's%20comment.%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20relevant%20'T'%20word%20here%20is%20terrorism%2C%20not%20tango%26quot%3B%2C%20during%20his%20weekly%20briefing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frelevant-t-word-is-terrorism-not-tango-india-on-pak-deputy-pms-remark-7393760%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kotak%20Mahindra%20Bank%20CTO%20%26amp%3B%20COO%20Milind%20Nagnur%20resigns%20citing%20personal%20reasons%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735920705000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fkotak-mahindra-bank-cto-coo-milind-nagnur-resigns-citing-personal-reasons-125010301117_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20resignation%20letter%2C%20Nagnur%20stated%20that%20he%20intends%20to%20relocate%20to%20the%20United%20States%20to%20care%20for%20family%20members%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22h